    WaveICA_2.0 batch correction

    bc_waveica.Rd

    This function returns a pmart object that has been undergone WaveICA_2.0 batch effect correction

    bc_waveica(omicsData, injection_cname, alpha = 0, cutoff = 0.1, K = 10)

    Arguments

    omicsData

    an object of the class 'pepData', 'proData', 'metabData', 'lipidData', or 'nmrData', usually created by as.pepData, as.proData, as.metabData, as.lipidData, or as.nmrData, respectively.

    injection_cname

    character string giving the name of the column in omicsData$f_data that contains the run order of the samples

    alpha

    tradeoff value between the independence of samples and those of variables in ICA, and should be between 0 and 1, defaults to 0

    cutoff

    threshold of the variation explained by the injection order for independent components, should be between 0 and 1, defaults to 0.1

    K

    maximal component that ICA decomposes, defaults to 10

    Value

    Object of same class as omicsData that has been undergone WaveICA normalization

    Author

    Damon Leach
